    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Indonesia: Militant Denies Role In Hotel Bombing</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By REUTERS</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Abu Dujana, high-ranking member of group Jeemah Islamiyah of Indonesia who was arrested June 9, tells Tempo magazine that he did not approve of and had no role in 2003 bombing of hotel in Jakarta; says Noordin Top, another militant, planned bombing, which killed 14 people (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Abu Dujana, a high-ranking militant who was arrested June 9, told Tempo magazine that he did not approve of the 2003 bombing of the J. W. Marriott hotel in Jakarta and had no role in planning it. Abu Dujana, who is believed to head a military wing of the group Jemaah Islamiyah, said Noordin Top, another militant, had planned the bombing, which killed 14 people.</p>
      </block>
